[
    {
        "content": "<p>I was looking at <a href=\"https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-parser\">https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-parser</a> again today for something and had a thought... should we revisit this API now that we have Record Builders?</p>",
        "id": 477166228,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1729069885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To be fair, <code>map</code> and <code>map2</code> are already defined for <code>Parser</code> in <code>Core</code>, so you can do everything you should need with those. Though we discovered the value of a static record builder field with <code>roc-random</code>, but you <em>also</em> have <code>const</code> in <code>Core</code>.</p>",
        "id": 477210844,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1729083928
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The difference is that we should maybe name  <code>Core</code> something more descriptive for default imports (<code>Core.map2</code> -&gt; <code>Parser.map2</code>), and consider aliasing <code>map2</code> to something like <code>chain</code> or <code>sequence</code> or <code>stringTogether</code>.</p>",
        "id": 477211840,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1729084241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which means we can have:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Zig\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">dateParser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">chain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">day</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">month</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">monthParser</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">year</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">date</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dateStr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">try</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">parse</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dateParser</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 477212531,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1729084484
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, looking at <code>Core.parse</code>, we should probably go through and rename all parsing functions in <code>Core</code> so that they make sense with a <code>Parser</code> prefix instead.</p>",
        "id": 477212796,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1729084568
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Something like <code>Parser.apply</code> and <code>Parser.applyPartial</code></p>",
        "id": 477212842,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1729084586
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd suggest <code>combine</code> or <code>build</code> instead of <code>chain</code>. To me, <code>chain</code> sounds like <code>andThen</code>/<code>bind</code>.</p>",
        "id": 477245680,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1729092937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or <code>batch</code> maybe?</p>",
        "id": 477245734,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1729092961
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, I like that one too</p>",
        "id": 477245956,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1729093025
    }
]